me of the core preoccupations of the psychoanalytic approach, she reveals how a religious and ethical relation to the “ordeal” of madness might actually allow for spiritual transformation. This sophisticated and evocative work illuminates new dimensions of psychoanalysis and the ethical imagination while also sensitively examining the collective psychic strife that so many communities endure today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aIslam and psychoanalysiszMorocco. 0aIslamzMoroccoxCustoms and practices. 0aMental healthxReligious aspectsxIslam. 0aMental illnessxAlternative treatmentzMorocco. 0aPastoral psychology (Islam). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aIslam.  aMorocco.  adespair.  amadness.  apsychoanalysis.  aspiritual transformation.  athe soul.  aunconscious.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311068858040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226465111423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226465111/original  a978-3-11-068858-0  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles